    IGES: { fullName: 'Initial Graphics Exchange Specification File', purpose: 'IGES is an older neutral standard for exchanging CAD wireframes, curves, trimmed surfaces, annotations, and some solid information.', stores: 'Its fixed-record text structure describes geometric entities, transformations, colors, layers, and drafting data.', compatibility: 'Many CAD systems still import IGES, but STEP generally transfers modern solid models and assemblies more reliably.', uses: ['Exchanging legacy surface models', 'Recovering historical CAD archives', 'Moving curves between design systems', 'Transferring older manufacturing geometry'], apps: ['FreeCAD', 'SOLIDWORKS', 'CATIA', 'Autodesk Inventor'], strength: 'Widely recognized for legacy curves and surface geometry', limitation: 'Imported surfaces may have gaps and assembly semantics are weak', conversion: 'Convert IGES to STEP or a native CAD format after sewing and healing surfaces. Verify tolerances, trims, units, and whether closed shells became valid solids.' },
