    Z: { fullName: 'Unix Compress File', purpose: 'Z is the legacy output of the Unix compress utility using LZW compression on one stream.', stores: 'It contains LZW-compressed data and a small header, usually representing one original file or a compressed TAR.', compatibility: 'Traditional Unix uncompress, gzip, and mature archive tools support .Z; modern workflows rarely create it.', uses: ['Opening legacy Unix downloads', 'Recovering old source packages', 'Migrating historical backups', 'Reading compressed manual resources'], apps: ['uncompress or gzip', '7-Zip', 'PeaZip'], strength: 'Compatible with historical Unix archives and tools', limitation: 'Obsolete compression and no native multi-file packaging', conversion: 'Decompress .Z first, then use gzip/xz for a stream or TAR/ZIP for multiple files. Check whether the recovered file is itself a TAR archive.' },
